The paper discusses the potential use of immersive augmented reality (IAR) in software engineering, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The paper also discusses the benefits of IAR in collaboration and communication, which relates to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of IAR in gaming and virtual reality, which relates to the virtual reality (cs.VR) category. The paper also discusses the potential security and privacy concerns of using IAR, which relates to the cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) category. Finally, the paper discusses the need for further research to make IAR a reality in software engineering, which relates to the social and information sciences (cs.SI) category.
